{\"video_title\":\"Game Play Pattern\",\"transcript\":\"вЂ‹One thing that I find really helpful when I'm trying to вЂ‹learn a new topic or improve my skills, вЂ‹I will just have fun is to play a game. вЂ‹When we can play games with вЂ‹new knowledge that we're trying to acquire, вЂ‹it's usually a fun way to really become вЂ‹masters of that knowledge and test our ability to use it. вЂ‹Particularly, the games are fun and challenging and вЂ‹so one of the patterns that we вЂ‹can use is called the gameplay pattern. вЂ‹The idea behind this pattern is вЂ‹we're going to ask ChatGPT вЂ‹or another large language model to play вЂ‹a game with us and it's going to decide the rules. вЂ‹It's going to be the game master in most cases. вЂ‹Now we can give it a variety of вЂ‹different scenarios that can вЂ‹govern what its role is in the game. вЂ‹But we're going to look at gameplay вЂ‹where the large language model вЂ‹is serving as the game master. вЂ‹It's creating the rules and it's driving the game. вЂ‹We can then take a game and we can say, вЂ‹I'd like a game on this topic or вЂ‹that has these basic rules fill in the rest. вЂ‹One of the things that's really nice вЂ‹about this is that if we say create вЂ‹a game and we give it вЂ‹some basic structure around the game, вЂ‹it can tap into its training data in вЂ‹order to populate the game with content. вЂ‹If you think about games like getting the rules right, вЂ‹obviously takes a lot of thought. вЂ‹But then there's a whole other challenge for a lot of вЂ‹games of how do you create a lot of вЂ‹great content to go with вЂ‹that game and so this is a pattern вЂ‹where we can tap into the training data from вЂ‹the large language model in order to вЂ‹help it populate the content. вЂ‹Now we can also do a pretty good job вЂ‹of deciding the rules as well вЂ‹but we're not going to necessarily look in вЂ‹these examples that complex rule generation. вЂ‹But we are going to look at вЂ‹a really useful example of this and I'm going to вЂ‹show you how to c